1
00:00:12,679 --> 00:00:14,723
Why are you drinking alone?

2
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:19,019
Wanted a drink that bad?

3
00:00:31,906 --> 00:00:35,201
Well, it's break time, we gotta party.

4
00:00:39,247 --> 00:00:40,415
Speaking of which...

5
00:00:40,665 --> 00:00:42,959
Wanna ditch this place and hit Itaewon?

6
00:00:47,505 --> 00:00:48,548
Nah, I’m good.

7
00:00:51,468 --> 00:00:52,927
Wanna go to Soo-hyuk’s place?

8
00:00:53,845 --> 00:00:55,221
No way, not going there.

9
00:00:56,639 --> 00:00:58,975
What? Something happen with your bro?

10
00:01:09,527 --> 00:01:10,945
Then let’s go somewhere else.

11
00:01:11,446 --> 00:01:13,281
Oh, I got a friend around here.

12
00:01:13,782 --> 00:01:14,741
Should I ask him to join?

13
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:17,827
Nah, let’s just drink by ourselves.

14
00:01:20,497 --> 00:01:23,958
What’s up, Lee Howon? Something’s off.

15
00:01:48,858 --> 00:01:50,110
3 months later

16
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:55,448
Hey, been doing okay over break?

17
00:01:56,699 --> 00:01:57,450
Uh... yeah.

18
00:01:58,284 --> 00:01:59,577
You didn’t even show up for drinks.

19
00:01:59,577 --> 00:02:00,787
Thought something happened.

20
00:02:01,746 --> 00:02:03,748
Nah, it’s nothing.

21
00:02:04,958 --> 00:02:06,960
I thought you were seriously sick or something.

22
00:02:07,877 --> 00:02:09,963
Semester’s started—we gotta grab a drink.

23
00:02:12,423 --> 00:02:13,466
We’ll see.

24
00:02:14,008 --> 00:02:15,927
Don’t “we’ll see” me.

25
00:02:15,927 --> 00:02:17,512
Let’s go out, for real.

26
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:21,891
- Hello.

27
00:02:21,891 --> 00:02:24,227
- I’m Minwoo Kim, and I’ll be teaching Big Data Management.

28
00:02:34,070 --> 00:02:36,072
That’s it for orientation.

29
00:02:36,948 --> 00:02:39,951
See you next class, everyone.

30
00:02:39,951 --> 00:02:41,286
Also, you there—

31
00:02:42,495 --> 00:02:43,955
Lee Howon?

32
00:02:49,419 --> 00:02:51,963
Come see me in my office.

33
00:03:00,138 --> 00:03:00,889
What the heck?

34
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:03,516
You already got in trouble?

35
00:03:16,237 --> 00:03:17,780
Yeah.

36
00:03:33,213 --> 00:03:34,881
Didn’t expect to see you again here.

37
00:03:40,887 --> 00:03:41,763
23 years old.

38
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:43,681
Lee Howon.

39
00:03:47,310 --> 00:03:49,062
Um, Professor—

40
00:03:52,690 --> 00:03:53,900
Just talk like before.

41
00:03:54,692 --> 00:03:56,194
Formal speech sounds weird from you.

42
00:03:57,904 --> 00:03:59,447
I’m really sorry.

43
00:04:00,406 --> 00:04:02,825
I didn’t think we’d run into each other again like this.

44
00:04:03,576 --> 00:04:05,620
So you lie to people you don’t expect to see again?

45
00:04:06,704 --> 00:04:08,248
That okay with you?

46
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:10,500
No...

47
00:04:10,875 --> 00:04:12,293
Of course not.

48
00:04:18,424 --> 00:04:20,468
So the time we spent together was fake too?

49
00:04:22,178 --> 00:04:23,471
Your age, your job—all fake?

50
00:04:26,849 --> 00:04:28,685
So basically, everything was a lie?

51
00:04:32,605 --> 00:04:35,483
You're not gonna mess with my grade or anything, right?

52
00:04:36,985 --> 00:04:37,694
Why?

53
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:40,738
Scared I might mess with you?

54
00:04:45,576 --> 00:04:48,204
- Well, you already did mess with me.

55
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:52,292
Shouldn't I get a chance to do the same?

56
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:05,680
At first, yeah, I was just playing around...

57
00:05:06,889 --> 00:05:08,641
But I really fell for you.

58
00:05:10,476 --> 00:05:12,937
I didn’t wanna see you disappointed in me.

59
00:05:13,521 --> 00:05:14,939
So I ran away.

60
00:05:25,366 --> 00:05:26,075
Go ahead.

61
00:05:26,993 --> 00:05:28,453
Apologize until I feel better.

62
00:05:29,454 --> 00:05:30,705
I’ll wait.

63
00:05:41,049 --> 00:05:42,425
I’m Lee Howon.

64
00:05:43,259 --> 00:05:46,387
I’m 23, and I’m a college student.

65
00:05:47,430 --> 00:05:49,724
I approached you because of a bet.

66
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:52,352
But I really did fall for you.

67
00:05:54,354 --> 00:05:56,564
I was scared you'd be disappointed in me.

68
00:05:58,066 --> 00:06:02,070
So I said something stupid and ran away.

69
00:06:03,905 --> 00:06:05,073
I’m sorry.

70
00:06:06,574 --> 00:06:08,493
This is how I really feel.

71
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:14,957
You think that’s enough to make me forgive you?

72
00:06:19,504 --> 00:06:21,506
I could go even further.

73
00:06:22,757 --> 00:06:23,758
Would that help?
